HEADWORD: Mishna
<hw>Mish"na</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NHeb.
<ets>mishn⟦amac⟧h</ets>, i. e., repetition, doubling, explanation (of
the divine law), fr. Heb. <ets>sh⟦amac⟧n⟦amac⟧h</ets> to change, to
repeat.]</ety> <def>A collection or digest of Jewish traditions and
explanations of Scripture, forming the text of the Talmud.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>Mischna</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

